@Node Description

	@{u}@{b}Short description of IconAct@{ub}@{uu}



IconAct is an appicon which recognize type of examined file and launch an utility associed to the finded type. Some features :
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Usage of FileClassPrefs for the identification of the differents file format.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Five utilities for one format.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Automatic assign for directories drop on the appicon.


IconAct is @{b}shareware@{ub} since 1.5. This version is not limited in any way, but if you like it, please support @{"The author" link Auteur} and consider to @{"register" link Register}.

@Endnode

@Node Installation "How install IconAct ?"

	@{u}@{b}Installation@{ub}@{uu}



No @{i}installer@{ui} script. Dont't panix, it's easy.

Fileclass.prefs used by IconAct is quite changed. So if you have a IconAct 1.0, you must copy :

 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}fileclass.prefs@{ui} dans @{i}ENV:@{ui}
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}fileclassprefs.catalog@{ui} dans @{i}LOCALE:catalogs/VotreLangue/@{ui}

@Endnode


@Node Config "Needed configuration"

	@{u}@{b}IconAct need :@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg fill}   @{bg background} OS 2.0 or greater.
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} ReqTools.library © Nico François.
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}FileClass.prefs@{ui}


	@{u}@{b}IconAct use if present :@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg fill}   @{bg background} The little but useful command @{i}xPK@{ui} by Urban Dominik Müller ( in @{i}c:@{ui} ).
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} L'option CrunchPatch de l'excellent @{i}MCP@{ui}. La reconnaissance des @{"fichiers compactés" link Compact} est alors totale.

@Endnode

@Node Utilisation "Usin IconAct" 

	@{u}@{b}Usage@{ub}@{uu}@



You just have to drop an icon on the appicon called IconAct. If the file type is recognized, the associated utility should be launch with the selected file as argument.

IconAct can make assign very simply. Just drag a directory or a volume on the appicon and enter an assign name.

You can reload preference file or quit IconAct by clicking on the appicon.


	@{b}Important@{ub}

Utilities are runned in CLI mode but don't stop the execution of IconAct. No output window is open, so execution of commands like lha is quite unusefull.

@Endnode

